sections.text:
In all classes, subject to the special provisions fo r each class and the tolerances allowed, the cobs of baby corn must be:  
- whole; 
- sound, produce affected by rotting or deterioration such as to make it unfit for consumption is 
excluded; 
- clean, practically free of any visible foreign matter; 
- free of damage caused by pests; 
- free of abnormal external moisture; 
- free of any foreign smell and/or taste; 
- fresh in appearance; 
- practically free of silk. 
The cut that is made on the base of the cobs should be clean and well defined.  A slight discolouration 
of the cut surface due to storage is acceptable.

